{
  "answer": "The ghazal is from *Diwan-E-Zauq* by Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, chapter 53 (\"baadam do jo bheje hain batwe mein daal kar\").[^1]\n\n**Matla (opening couplet):**  \nThese almonds that you sent, a gift however small,  \nMy faith demands I give my eyes and answer to the call.[^2]\n\n**Potter's-wheel couplet:**  \nNo perfect vessel from the wheel will form at all,  \nSo do not waste this heart-dust on the potter's call.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, chapter 53.\n[^2]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/53-baadam-do-jo-bheje-hain-batwe-mein-daal-kar/translation/#p-d86b48).\n[^3]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/53-baadam-do-jo-bheje-hain-batwe-mein-daal-kar/translation/#p-290709).",
